The paper deals with a problem in distributed computing, specifically in the Population Protocols model, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The problem involves graph-based computation and memory constraints, which are also relevant to the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves algorithm design and analysis, which are relevant to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves information theory, specifically in terms of lower bounds on memory complexity, which is relevant to the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT).
